basics.label: Healthcare Clinical Analyst
basics.summary: Experienced Healthcare Clinical Analyst with a demonstrated history of working in the medical field. Skilled in administrative management, medical procedure implementation, medication handling, and patient care coordination.

work.name: Company Name
work.position: Oncology Nurse, Manager, Research Coordinator, Healthcare Clinical Analyst, GI Infusion Nurse, FAST Program Coordinator, Clinical Research Coordinator
work.summary: Involved in various responsibilities from being a healthcare analyst to a manager for a healthcare study. Administered different types of therapy and medication as a nurse. Managed an implementation of QA program. Also responsible for grant writing and management. Served as the principal investigator for a study of complementary/unconventional cancer therapies.
highlights: Entered the insurance arena with no insurance experience and successfully served as a leader in the appeals deparement.
Created training manuals and mentored new employees, and provided constant process improvement.
Managed a staff of over thirty employees including data collectors and ancillary staff for a National Childre'n's Study.
Developed and implanted the QA program.
Prepared statistical reports for the principal investigator and identified trends and areas for quality assurance implementation.
Administered immunoglobulin therapy, chemotherapy, blood products, hydration and pain medication.
Educated patients and families regarding medications, drug processes and navigating the healthcare system.
